menu "Paperboy Audio"

    config PAPERBOY_BUZZER_GPIO
        int "Buzzer GPIO number"
        default 45
        help
            GPIO pin connected to the M5PaperS3 passive buzzer.
            The I2S PDM TX bitstream is output on this pin; an RC low-pass
            filter (e.g. 100 Ω + 100 nF) between the pin and the buzzer
            recovers the audio waveform.

    config PAPERBOY_AUDIO_RING_FRAMES
        int "Audio ring buffer size in GB frames"
        default 6
        range 2 16
        help
            Number of Game Boy audio frames to buffer.  Each frame is ~550
            mono samples (~16.8 ms at 32768 Hz).  Larger values absorb more
            emulation jitter at the cost of latency.

endmenu
